programme.title: EFL Cup Highlights
programme.sub-title: Carling Cup Final 2008/09: Manchester United v Tottenham Hotspur.
programme.desc: Manchester United v Tottenham Hotspur. Action from the showpiece encounter at Wembley Stadium, where the first major trophy of the season was contested. Spurs were the holders, having defeated Chelsea 2-1 after extra time in last year's final, while the Red Devils had last lifted the cup in 2006 following a comfortable 4-0 win against Wigan Athletic

programme.title: EFL Cup Highlights
programme.sub-title: Carling Cup Final 2009/10: Aston Villa v Manchester United.
programme.desc: Aston Villa v Manchester United. Action from the showpiece match at Wembley Stadium

programme.title: EFL Cup Highlights
programme.sub-title: Carling Cup Final 2010/11: Arsenal v Birmingham City.
programme.desc: Arsenal v Birmingham City. Extended highlights of the showpiece match at Wembley Stadium, where the winner of the first major trophy of the 2010/11 season was decided. Arsenal started as strong favourites to win their first silverware since they lifted the FA Cup in the 2004/05 campaign and had already defeated the Blues home and away in the Premier League during the season. However, Alex McLeish's men demonstrated their resolve when overcoming Aston Villa and West Ham United in the previous two rounds and will have been eager to produce an upset

programme.title: EFL Cup Highlights
programme.sub-title: Carling Cup Final 2011/12: Cardiff City v Liverpool.
programme.desc: Liverpool v Cardiff City. Action from the showpiece match at Wembley Stadium, where the winner of the first major trophy of the 2011/12 season was decided. The Reds had defeated the likes of Stoke City, Chelsea and Manchester City to reach the final and went into the match as clear favourites in their first visit to the national stadium since it was rebuilt. However, the Bluebirds, who defeated Crystal Palace on penalties in the semi-finals, had been in good form in the Championship and will have fancied their chances of producing an upset

programme.title: EFL Cup Highlights
programme.sub-title: Capital One Cup Final 2012/13: Bradford City v Swansea City.
programme.desc: Bradford City v Swansea City. Highlights from Wembley Stadium, where the League Two Bantams were aiming to produce yet another cup upset. Swansea were appearing in their first major cup final and beat Chelsea in the semi-finals to reach this stage, but Bradford had stolen most of the headlines in the competition this season, belying their lowly league status to eliminate the likes of Arsenal, Aston Villa and Wigan Athletic

programme.title: EFL Cup Highlights
programme.sub-title: Capital One Cup Final 2013/14: Manchester City v Sunderland.
programme.desc: Manchester City v Sunderland. Highlights of the showpiece occasion at Wembley Stadium, where the first major domestic silverware of the 2013/14 season was decided. City started as clear favourites as they continued their quest for trophies, but the Black Cats could take heart from their impressive recent record against their big-spending opponents, albeit in home matches, and the fact that they had already eliminated Chelsea and Manchester United from this season's competition
